Uses of Package
sbw.architecture.bus.protocol

Packages that use sbw.architecture.bus.protocol
Package
Description
sbw.architecture.bus
Contains the elements of a general-purpose communication bus.
sbw.architecture.bus.protocol
Contains the elements of the communication protocols for a bus.
sbw.architecture.support
Contains support classes shared by the overall system.
sbw.project.cli.action
Contains support classes shared by the overall system.
sbw.project.components.actuator
Contains the actuators.
sbw.project.components.actuator.aileron
Contains the aileron actuators.

Contains the engine actuators.

Contains the flap actuators.

Contains the rudder actuators.

Contains the actuator controllers.
  • Classes in sbw.architecture.bus.protocol used by sbw.architecture.bus
    Class
    Description
    A_Payload
    Defines the shared elements of a payload, which is a wrapper around arbitrary contents to be included with requests.
    A_Request
    Defines the shared elements of a bus request, which defines a desired action to be considered by a servicer on a bus.
    I_Identifiable
    Defines a contract for any class that allows itself to be identified by an Identifier.
    I_Servicer
    Defines the contract that a servicer must follow to connect to a bus.
    Notification
    Defines a notification to a I_Servicer on a Bus when it receives an update from the BusManager on a clock event.
    RequestCancel
    Defines a request to cancel an existing request on a servicer immediately without any opportunity to shut it down gracefully.
    RequestInform
    Defines a request to a servicer to supply arbitrary data to be returned to the requester in a visitor bucket.
    RequestService
    Defines a request to have a servicer do something with a given payload at a defined.
    RequestTerminate
    Defines a request to cancel an existing request on a servicer by shutting it down gracefully and canceling it as soon as possible.
    Response
    Defines a response from submitting a A_Request to a I_Servicer on a Bus.
